description.narrative: 70,670 children, their caregivers, community members and local authorities developed capacities to improve protective factors in their communities and reduce violence against children through resilience-building activities and improved abilities to identify and report violence against children to the authorities in 40 cities. In the most violent communities, UNICEF has adopted the Cure Violence methodology, training volunteer violence interrupters and strengthening community-based organizations to identify risk factors, understand power dynamics, apply techniques to stop violence and prevent homicide, mediating conflicts through cooperation, adolescent and youth participation and community mobilization. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:14/01/2020
